business reaction[edit],"the international air transport association, whose 230 member airlines comprise 93% of all international traffic, position is that trading should be based on ""benchmarking"", setting emissions levels based on industry averages, rather than ""grandfathering"", which would use individual companies' previous emissions levels to set their future permit allowances. they argue grandfathering ""would penalise airlines that took early action to modernise their fleets, while a benchmarking approach, if designed properly, would reward more efficient operations"".[42]
