economics[edit],"it is possible for a country to reduce emissions using a command-and-control approach, such as regulation, direct and indirect taxes. the cost of that approach differs between countries because the marginal abatement cost curve (mac)—the cost of eliminating an additional unit of pollution—differs by country.
